address.streetAddress: Corner of 24th Ave NW & NW 67th St

name: Meditative Mountain Hike
description: Lets get out of the city and inhale the ridiculous beauty of the PNW. Gain healing wisdom from Mother Earth and reconnect with your own inner, still voice during a guided meditation and a silent 3 mile, low elevation gain hike. We'll debrief the victories and defeats discovered and leave with a clear mind and a game plan to soothe the day-to-day craziness of being human.

review.name: Camino Frances with Walks in Spain....An Amazing Journey!
review.reviewBody: Thank you so much Walks in Spain (Paul) for an amazing and unforgettable experience we had on the Camino.  You have definitely given my family and I a taste of Spain through the variety of accommodations you booked for us. They were all great and unique in their own way.  Your unending support on our self-guided tour and helpful packets with maps and tips has made our walk go smoothly. As I journey through the Camino, I see life in itself. I’m so glad that I had the opportunity to do this and would do it again (perhaps the Camino Portuguese) with Walks in Spain. Thank you and I appreciate you! God bless you!

review.name: The Camino will change you
review.reviewBody: The Camino will change you. There are 2 journeys,the outer and the inner.Pre journey please read,'the pilgrim way of Saint James by David Baldwin and Contemplating the Camino by Brendan McManus SJ and watch the Camino film 'The way'.In 2018 did it from the east the last 100 + km,In 2019 from the south.Plan to do from the west in 2020 and from the North in 2021. Hopefully Ignatian Camino from Loyola to Manresa in 2022.

review.name: Walks in Spain provided excellent service
review.reviewBody: I walked with 5 other adult family members the last 100k of the Camino (French route), from Sarria. From start to finish, Paul was helpful and informative, and gave us great advice. The accommodations and recommended stops along the way were A+. If you have time, the detour to Vilar de Donas is worth the walk; 1 91-year-old man patiently explained (for our limited Spanish) the interesting architecture, sculpture, theological art of the chapel. I cannot recommend Walks in Spain highly enough.

review.name: Paul’s the BEST!!
review.reviewBody:
We used Walks in Spain with Paul as our master of planning.  He really took care of us.  He replied quickly and with all the information requested plus more.  Our accommodations were top notch and the food was so bountiful.  He arranged train, taxi and trip went on without an issue.
The Camiño is magical and to have this be our first experience went so well, I am planning on doing it next year.
Thank you to Paul and his attention to detail.  He is one sharp traveler.

review.name: Astorga to Sarria - Walks in Spain Nailed it -- Again!
review.reviewBody: We had such a great experience in 2018 (Sarria to Santiago) that we came back in 2019 to walk the 100 miles from Astorga to Sarria. Completely different vibe and much more challenging walk, but the ambiance and "feel" of the Camino remained the same. Walks in Spain once again took care of the details so we could simply concentrate on our walk. Every detail was taken care of and the self-guided instructions that were provided were perfect. If you are considering walking in Spain and wish to engage the services of a great company, contact Paul @ Walks in Spain.

review.name: Booked with Walks In Spain
review.reviewBody: El Camino is one of those things that you plan to do your whole life, but it is the precious few who make that happen NOW. I recommend you take this hike during May and that you book the trip with Walks In Spain. They make everything so easy, booking the whole trip for you and planning the entire route perfectly. May is the best time of the season because of the weather - crisp and cool at night and in the mornings, and a bit spicy hot during the day.

itemListElement.name: Scenic Seattle Sunset Views and Nightlife in Neighborhoods

name: Scenic Seattle Sunset Views and Nightlife in Neighborhoods
description: Enjoy Seattle by night in the great old neighborhood, Ballard on Puget Sound - just 5 miles from downtown. We first view downtown Seattle at Kerry Park and then drive to Golden Gardens Park where we stroll the beach for the sunset. Then we go to a few popular bars in old historic town of Ballard. Here you have an opportunity to buy something to drink and experience some nightlife. A both scenic and fun cultural night with great views of Seattle and Puget Sound.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Scavenger Hunt Walking Tour and Game

name: Seattle Scavenger Hunt Walking Tour and Game
description:
Embark on an intriguing scavenger hunt through the vibrant heart of downtown Seattle!. Discover the charm of the happening Seattle center, the bustling Pike Place market, and the beautiful downtown and waterfront. Explore the iconic sights such as the first Starbucks location, the Space Needle, the Great Wheel and much more.

Dive into the eclectic array of unique artisan shops, welcoming eateries, and captivating Seattle culture. Explore at your own pace and experience the best of what Seattle has to offer. Ready to explore Seattle from a fresh perspective? Let the adventure begin!

name: Elliott Bay Sea Kayak Tour
description: Our local knowledgeable guides, with years of experience will take you on an incredible journey through the Elliot Bay. You will experience and unbeatable Seattle skyline view overlooking the sound. We are located minutes away from our sandy Alki Beach. There will be beautiful views of the Cascade and Olympic Mountain ranges as well as a chance to see marine wildlife.

review.name: Great for groups!
review.reviewBody: Gill and his team planned a memorable and super fun kayaking experience as a part of our girls' day out for group of about 15 ladies!! We were also impressed with how smooth everything went and Gill and the team were extremely friendly and helpful the entire process! The location was very convenient and there's a nice restroom, lockers, and foot showers right there. All of the ladies in our group had a great time and we are very thankful to Alki Kayak Tours for making our day extra special!

itemListElement.name: 4 Day Seattle City and the Verdant Landscapes of Washington State

name: 4 Day Seattle City and the Verdant Landscapes of Washington State
description: Join our local expert trip leader on a captivating 4-day journey through the lush landscapes of Seattle and Washington State, immersing yourself in natural wonders and cultural gems. Day one begins with a vibrant exploration of Seattle's iconic Pike Place Market, bustling with local flavors and artisanal delights. We then ascend the Space Needle at the Seattle Center for panoramic city views before strolling along the picturesque waterfront. On day two, we venture into the serene countryside to witness the beauty of Snoqualmie Falls and savor the exquisite wines of the surrounding wine country. Day three leads us to Diablo Lake in North Cascades National Park, where emerald waters reflect the towering peaks. Finally, on day four, we embark on a scenic ferry ride to tranquil Bainbridge Island. This enchanting tour promises an unforgettable blend of urban exploration and natural splendor, showcasing the best of Seattle and Washington State's lush beauty.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Walking Tour - Georgetown Art & Old Rainier Beer District

name: Seattle Walking Tour - Georgetown Art & Old Rainier Beer District
description:
This a brewery walking tour through the Georgetown neighborhood in Seattle. Georgetown is one of the most fascinating and often overlooked neighborhoods in the city. With a rich history in industry, brewing, and the arts, this tour is perfect for visitors looking to dig a little deeper. It is also great for those new to the city or those who have lived here a while and want to learn some more of Seattle's secrets. Your guide will be well versed in the Seattle art scene and have plenty of shopping and food and drink recommendations.
This is a walking tour and we cover roughly 2.5 miles on foot. The tour will take place rain or shine, (we only cancel during weather advisories). We recommend you dress appropriately, including footwear.

itemListElement.name: Passenger Ferry between Seattle & San Juan Island ONE-WAY

name: Passenger Ferry between Seattle & San Juan Island ONE-WAY
description:
Skip the traffic and Anacortes ferry lines and hop on the San Juan Clipper ferry for the fastest way to travel direct from Pier 69 in Seattle to San Juan Island for a visit to beautiful Friday Harbor, WA!

The 3 hours and 45 minutes ferry ride through the Salish Sea will take you past Whidbey Island and underneath historic Deception Pass bridge before arriving in Friday Harbor. Upon arrival, you’ll be steps from Friday Harbor's charming downtown.

Please Note: This is ONE-WAY only. Please book 2nd leg of trip for your desired return time.

review.name: Efficient and cost effective
review.reviewBody: Be prepared for a ten minute walk from the upper parking lot to the terminal.  Other than that, the experience was pleasant.

description:
SPACE NEEDLE TICKET IS INCLUDED!!!
You will see the most iconic foresights of Seattle.
You will know unique things from locals.

Unforgettable experience and lowest price for you!

itemListElement.name: FEAST - Favorite Eats Asian Style Tour

name: FEAST - Favorite Eats Asian Style Tour
description: The Favorite Eats Asian Style Tour "FEAST" is a two hour eating and walking tour of the Seattle International District. We will start with dim sum at my favorite Chinese restaurant where you will sample a delightful array of small plates . After eating brunch we will walk through the International District to a Chinese bakery for dessert and end the tour with bubble tea; The walking tour will take you through Chinatown, Little Saigon and Nihonmachi (Japantown). Every tour will include an overview of the history of Seattle's International District and a map listing all my favorite restaurants so you can return on your own to keep exploring. I will give you recommendations and information you need to discover and enjoy this amazing and unique part of Seattle.

review.name: Great way to visit one of Seattle's best neighborhoods!
review.reviewBody: If you get a chance to take Violet's tour, do it!  Her tour is a great way to explore the neighborhood and the yummy food.  Sure, you can explore on your own.  But why would you?  With Violet, you get insider tips on the best places to eat, a bit of history of the neighborhood, and help ordering a bubble tea (if you haven't tried one yet).  Fun for all ages - not too much walking for youngsters or creaky knees.  Whether you are a long time Seattlite or a first time visitor, you will learn something new and leave with a happy stomach.

name: Fishing Charters
description: We offer a fun filled day with a very helpful and engaging guide. From beginners to Pro's and young or old, we will do or best to make sure you have the best day on the water.

itemListElement.name: Private Photo Session with a Local Photographer in Seattle

name: Private Photo Session with a Local Photographer in Seattle
description:
Want to capture your amazing honeymoon? Family vacation while the kids are still little? Your perfect couples retreat from everyday busy life? A solo trip without asking strangers to take pictures of you? Stop searching, we got you here!
We are the largest network of local vacation photographers in the world! Besides Seattle, we operate in over 700 destinations worldwide! We always make sure that every special moment of each client is captured well. 
We believe in our service and quality of our photos so much that we even offer a 100% money back satisfaction guarantee for your photo shoot. Which means, if you don’t like the result of your photo shoot, you can contact us within 7 days and claim your money back!
So what are you waiting for? Become one of our hundreds of happy customers by treating yourself to this special experience! Your family and friends will love the result too!

itemListElement.name: Hurricane Ridge Olympic National Park from Seattle

name: Hurricane Ridge Olympic National Park from Seattle
description:
PRIVATE tour for your group only.
- Ferry ride across Puget Sound
- Clean and comfortable 6 passenger SUV
- Hurricane Ridge (note 2023 Upper Visitor Center is closed)
- Native American owned deli 
- Magnificent views and various trails

review.name: Incredible visit to Olympic National Park
review.reviewBody:
We went in late April and there had been so much snow that seeing Hurricane Ridge wasn’t possible. So, we went into the south of the park and enjoyed 2 incredible hikes through the temperate rain forest. Surreal landscape with towering trees, moss covered vegetation and pristine streams. 
Cheryl is extremely knowledgeable and very conversant in all aspects of Olympic National Park. Good driver. Comfortable transportation. 
Highly recommended.

review.name: Heavenly Views and Awesome Company!
review.reviewBody: We actually did two trips with Cheryl's Northwest Tours in August 2022 (Mt Rainier and Hurricane Ridge). We absolutely had great time with Dan and Cheryl. The weather was awesome and the views were heavenly! Cheryl gets to know you and your family and customizes the trip according to your interests and needs. She and her tour operators cover everything from history, botany, geology of the area to fun facts, while remaining flexible based on the specific circumstances of the day. Cheryl knows how to get to the best views as quickly as possible so that we can enjoy our trip. as a matter of fact, we just didn't want to leave Hurricane ridge or Mt. Rainier because it was nature at its best. The pictures on Cheryl's website are not photoshopped- the views are as gorgeous as they look like on the website. In addition, Cheryl is great at conversations-we loved our time with her. Highly recommend these two trips-we might go back again with Cheryl since there is so much to still explore!

review.name: A great day in Olympic National Park
review.reviewBody: We had an excellent experience visiting Hurricane Ridge and Marymere Falls in Olympic National Park. Cheryl made us feel at home right away and conversation flowed easily, turning the day into a great family outing. We learnt a lot about both Seattle and the parks. The SUV was clean and comfortable, and the snacks were great! Cheryl was also very mindful of our time constraints. We recommend her highly!

review.name: Not reliable
review.reviewBody: Cancelled in the last moment without saying any reason. I was really disappointed. I never recommend.

review.name: Olympic National Park
review.reviewBody: We had a great time with Cheryl on our tour to Hurricane Ridge. She is very personable to be with for all day trip. Her car was clean and organized and comfortable for a day trip. She gives enough information without overwhleming with the guests. We were able to stop and grab some sandwiches at a local restuarant/gas station and they were delicious. She stops where ever you want for pictures and doesn't rush you along. We were able to have a great day with amazing views all without having to drive. We would recommended doing a private tour with Cheryl anytime you are in Seattle!

review.name: Great guide, great service.
review.reviewBody: Cheryl was fabulous. Snacks provided for our long ride, very informative about so very much. A great day of rain and cold in the rainforest. Cheryl was our sunshine!

review.name: Great tour of Hurricane Ridge
review.reviewBody:
Cheryl runs a FANTASTIC operation. I had a payment issue come up (long story) but she was extremely accomodating and bent over backwards to make it work. I had been eyeing this tour for a while but there was still a decent amount of snow in the beginning of May but she kept her ear to the ground just for me to let me know it was doable.
My guide was Janet and she was an absolute delight. She filled the trip with so many fun facts and of course knew her way around the area and route so I didn't have to mess with it. I was picked up in an SUV with plenty of healthy snacks (which was great as I had skipped breakfast) as well as bottles of water. Before we made our way up we stopped at a small cafe and picked up some sandwiches and had a lovely picnic up at the top with the STUNNING backdrop of the mountains behind us. Thankfully Janet knew the routes well enough that even with a decent amount of snow she still had her bearings and knew were was safe to walk and took a few pics of me. 
If I'm in the area again and want to see the parks/outdoors I'm using her, highly recommend.

review.name: Highly recommended
review.reviewBody: I was very satisfied with the private tour. Cheryl was very decent, thoughtful and professional, and was the best guide I've ever met. The car was comfortable and everything was clean and perfectly ready. The scenery of the mountain was great and the time at the drive-through zoo was very enjoyable. I'd like to ask her to guide me again when I go to there next time.

itemListElement.name: Dough Zone Dumpling House - Seattle Pine Street

name: Dough Zone Dumpling House - Seattle Pine Street
One-Way Transfer: Pier 91 to Airport
description:
With over 25 years of safely transporting 500K+ cruise ship passengers you can rest assured that Seattle Express is the best option for you and your family. 

Save 30% to 40% off the cost of your airport transfer with our shared shuttle service. We offer direct service to the airport departing on demand between 7AM to 11AM ensuring you get to the airport on time. 

We're the top-rated ground transportation provider in Seattle! 

Safe, Affordable and Convenient service makes Seattle Express an easy choice.

review.name: Very unorganized
review.reviewBody: We booked the cruise terminal to an airport hotel. We waited until 9am to disembark the ship and proceed down to bus spot R (at very end loading lot) When we arrived, people were already waiting and said the shuttle had left at 9am. The next bus did not arrive until after 10:15. The attendant apologized and said there was confusion with the ports after blaming it on traffic issues. We waited for over an hour standing outside. When the buses arrived, they had to unload passengers and luggage for people coming on the next cruise as it was time that the new passengers could arrive. I would not use them for transportation to the airport to catch a flight in the morning as they are very unorganized.

review.name: Best shuttle service from cruise ship to SeaTac
review.reviewBody: Best way to transfer between cruise ship and SeaTac. Cheaper than Uber and Carnival shuttle. Driver in parking lot when we got off and only waited maybe 10 minutes before departure.

review.name: Will use again and again!
review.reviewBody: It was awesome to walk past huge lines at the cruise port in Seattle and get right on the Seattle express. Excellent driver and transport.

review.name: Communicated pickup instructions and delivered
review.reviewBody: Convenient pickup and communication.  Delivered quickly to airport in a comfortable, courteous and professional manner.

review.name: Great service at a great price
review.reviewBody: We booked pick-up from the cruise port for transfer to an airport hotel. The instructions for meeting the shuttle at Pier 91 were excellent. Check-in was easy and fast. The driver was friendly and helpful, and got us to our hotel quickly and efficiently.  Great experience with this company!

review.name: Great Experience after having a great experience
review.reviewBody:
I was pleased with the service and the staff were there at the time I was promised...quick load and go to the airport.  The staff were great, sorry I can't recall their names but they took my luggage, got me on the transfer bus and once we were all loaded, we were on our way.
We were taken to the airport first, then those that were on their way to a hotel were taken so that no one would miss their flight time.
I would definitely use this service again.

review.name: Pugsley the tour guide!
review.reviewBody: Jeff “Pugsley” was friendly and efficient. He reviewed his route and stops, upon departure from the port, so that guests were aware.  He pointed out many notable sites along the way, that we wouldn’t have learned about otherwise (ie: Starbucks HQ and the Boeing building ( including the history of Boeing). We would definitely use this service again, if needed!

review.name: Easy peasy
review.reviewBody: The easiest way to get to the airport from the cruise pier. Bus was comfortable, clean and our driver even shared the history of the Seattle landmarks as we traveled.

review.name: Great Service
review.reviewBody: Airport To Pier 91 Simon (9-16) the driver was very informative about local sites. Left Pier to airport driver was very friends. We purchased round trip prior to debarkment. Highly recommend!

review.name: Port to airport transfer
review.reviewBody: Very efficient and smooth ride to the airport. Easy to book via Trip Advisor app and reasonably priced.  You’ll receive a text with details on what bus lane and the time slot so you know where to go after debarking the ship.  Pugsley was a very knowledgeable and friendly driver!

name: Yellowstone Grand Teton and Coeur d’Alene 5-Day Tour from Seattle
description:
Visit the smallest host city of the World Expo Spokane and visit 50,000 Silver Dollar Collection Bar.
Take a visit to Yellowstone National Park and Grand Teton National Park to enjoy the geothermal wonders and other beautiful sceneries!
Lake View Wooden House Terra Nova is specially arranged at two nights.

review.name: Experience of Yellowstone and Grand Teton - Supurb
review.reviewBody: The 5 day trip to Yellowstone and Grand Teton National Parks from Seattle from 10th to 14th September 2023 was amazing. Our tour guide Joelin was excellent and ensured that all of us were very comfortable and the tour coverage was very comprehensive. My rating for Howling is 5/5 . However the bus in which we travelled was very small and old and there was no space to keep your hand luggage. The door of the bus was was opening with difficulty. If the bus where we spent 5 days was better, I would have given a 5/5 rating. In any case I would recommend this trip strongly

review.name: An Unforgettable Journey into the 1st Nature Wonderland- Yellowstone Nation Park
review.reviewBody:
We have booked this tour in early August 2023 from Vancouver. I am always willing to visit Yellowstone, to check out the amazing nature view, history, geology and ecology. 
During the tour, the tour guide was knowledgeable and passionate, and accommodations were comfortable, with the special 2-night lake view cable near Yellowstone Park. 
The logistics included transportation and the route line was well-planned, with enough time to have a deep visit to each famous viewpoints. 
Thanks to the experience of the tour guide, we had the most valuable photos, it made my dream come true. We captured the stunning landscapes and wildlife. He always helped the photographers to get the best shots. 

Overall, Thanks to the tour guide Mr.Joe Lin, the amazing experience left me with lasting memories and I appreciate the wonder of the world.

review.name: Best Group Trip
review.reviewBody:
One of the best experiences of a lifetime. We saw animals such as moose, bison (plenty of them), and elks. There were so many hot springs as well as geysers to be amazed by. Yellowstone National Park is just very impressive.
Oh and our guide Zhou Lin was so kind, patient with everybody, a good driver, and very knowledgeable. 
Would definitely recommend.

review.name: Great
review.reviewBody: Im elderly ơn a wheelchair and enjoyed my time ! So happy to see Yellowstone.  ‘I’ve staff . Saw so much on this trip !

itemListElement.name: Viator Exclusive - Half Day Mountain Bike Tour from Seattle

name: Viator Exclusive - Half Day Mountain Bike Tour from Seattle
description: Join a mountain bike tour with an instructor certified bike guide! With a guest to guide ratio of 4:1, you'll be sure to get focused guiding on your small group tour. Explore the beauty of the Pacific Northwest in a way that most travelers don't get to!

review.name: Really fun
review.reviewBody: This was really fun and we had a great tour guide. The forest was beautiful. Beginners can do this but some experience is better. You do need to be in moderately good shape.

review.name: Great trails. Great bikes. Great scenery.
review.reviewBody:
The guide (Erik) was great. Personable and knowledge about the area. He found a few different trail options with varied terrain and difficulty. 

The dual suspension cabin rides were great too!

If you are in the Seattle area and want to get out on some great trails I definitely recommend checking this tour out.

review.name: Tiger Rocks
review.reviewBody: DJ was great - fun, supportive, loves mountain biking and picked great trails.  Rode Tiger mountain - awesome and beautiful - totally different from riding in Pennsylvania- wanna do it again soon.

itemListElement.name: Chihuly Garden and Glass in Seattle Ticket

name: Chihuly Garden and Glass in Seattle Ticket
description:
- Only long-term Exhibition that showcases artist Dale Chihuly’s work

- Located at Seattle Center

- Free digital photos 

- Free audio tour 

- Unique space with a garden & glasshouse

- Live glass demonstrations year-round

- Everything included in the ticket – no upcharges for smartphone audio tour, gallery talks, live glass demonstrations. 

- Garden is vibrant during all four seasons – spring and fall are particularly unique times in the ever-changing Garden.

review.name: AWESOME!
review.reviewBody: Beautiful glass and gardens. Highly recommend. We enjoyed the gardens as much as the museum. Also enjoyed the glass blowing demo.

review.name: Explosion of Color in Carious Forms.
review.reviewBody: Breathtaking, bright, beautiful colors, exceptional take on the sea, flowers, and life through an artists eyes. Inside and outside, you are treated to an array of color and forms. Loved it!!!!

review.name: Must visit
review.reviewBody: Beautiful exhibit!  Must visit.  Convenient they have a photographer on site and they make it very easy to retrieve your FREE photos.

review.name: So much beauty!
review.reviewBody: Works so beautiful, they took my breath away. Self paced walk through the museum and garden allows the viewer to enjoy each display in their own time. Theater shows multiple videos of different periods in his life. Very interesting!

review.name: What a view!
review.reviewBody:
We really enjoyed the Space needle.  This is always a great way to see a city - from up above the skyline.  It was a clear day so we were blessed to see Mt Rainier too.

We enjoyed a drink in the revolving observatory deck and got some GREAT pictures.  A very memorable experience.

review.name: Beautiful
review.reviewBody: Beautiful, next to the Needle in Seattle, unusual glass sculptures in a museum setting.  Has a nice outdoor seating for food and drinks

review.name: Amazing experience!
review.reviewBody: Amazing experience! The view was breath-taking and the art was INSPIRING!! I was able to check out a wheel chair at the Space Needle for my husband with mobility issues. It wa very helpful to see the Chihuly especially.

review.name: A bit disappointed
review.reviewBody: Chihuly’s teams work is impressive.  I visited the St. Petersburg, Fla exhibit in February and was looking forward to this exhibition.  The indoor exhibit was similar to the St. Petersburg exhibit, still beautiful but I was expecting something different.  I was expecting an expansive outdoor display such as the floating glass orbs that was repeatedly shown on the films about his life in the indoor theatre.  The outdoor displays were, once again, impressive and beautiful with the color and manipulation of glass.  I was expecting that the gardens would be more expansive than they were.

review.name: Very recommended for people who live gardens and art
review.reviewBody: Amazingly creative and beautiful. Each room and the garden were awe inspiring.  The glass blowing demo was very interesting.  The movies of past exhibits were very interesting and let you see who the artist is and how he works and creates.  So interesting!

review.name: AWESOME!!!!!
review.reviewBody: The view was amazing! It was expensive, but worth it. The view totally made up for it! There was a cute little gift shop below! Definitely reccomend!

itemListElement.name: Viator Exclusive-Snoqualmie Tunnel MTN Bike Tour from Seattle

name: Viator Exclusive-Snoqualmie Tunnel MTN Bike Tour from Seattle
description: Explore the Pacific Northwest as you've never before! This unique excursion is one that few travelers to Washington get to experience and will leave you with long-lasting memories. The Snoqualmie tunnel is a local favorite, and you'll definitely see why!

review.name: A Fun + Steady Decline
review.reviewBody: How did I not know such a great trail existed near Seattle? I had a great time with SMB Tours riding on the Snoqualmie Tunnel Tour. They outfitted us with mountain bikes, lights, and helmets and then we were off. Spending a few hours amongst the forests, wild flowers, and mountains on a nice steady decline made for a pleasant ride! No hills, just fun! DJ was great at checking in with the group and making sure we had what we needed.

review.name: The Snoqualmie Tunnel Tour is AMAZING!
review.reviewBody: The Snoqualmie Tunnel Tour with Seattle Mountain Bike Tours is AMAZING! It starts with a very tunnel cool ride through the middle of a mountain - WOW! The mountain views are beautiful from the elevated rail trail as you (mostly) coast downhill from Snoqualmie Pass. DJ is an excellent guide, providing just the right amount of historical information and humor! Highly recommended for anyone looking for a unique, active tour while visiting Seattle.

review.name: Amazing Tunnel Bike Ride!
review.reviewBody: Had an amazing experience on this bike trail that we have wanted to ride for many years. Seattle Mountain Bikes Tours ran a great tour. Our bikes were in excellent condition with great shocks and chosen to fit our height. A bike light for the tunnel, water bottle and snacks were provided. We had so much fun and it was a beautiful ride. Thank you SMBT!

review.name: Best Day Trip On A Bicycle ANYWHERE
review.reviewBody: My wife and I had a fantastic time riding the trail from Hyak down to Cedar Falls.  I've made that trip many times, including 4 times on a train a long, long time ago and many more times on a bike.  Seattle Mountain Bike Tours knows how to make it a great event with fun and well-informed guides.  Remember to wear layers of clothing; my wife said the tunnel is like riding a bike through a refrigerator!

review.name: Great Ride! 100 percent worth it!
review.reviewBody:
Had a blast! Spen a half day exploring great, flowy trails. I'd never ridden trails like these, and really enjoyed the time out on the bike. Trails offered a good variety of features. It was rainy the day I rode (of course!)  but the trails were well-drained and very ridable. We got muddy, yep, but not enough to keep us from having an absolute blast!

Our tour guide was great. Me being a beginner rider unfamiliar with  the  area and the features, I felt totally confident that DJ understood where riders were at in terms  of ability.. He  lead us on beautiful, flowy trails that introduced us to features that were both challenging and super fun to ride!

Highly recommend this tour! Well worth the time & the ticket!  I would definitely do it again!

review.name: EPIC Scenery, Hospitality, and Gratifying Mountain Bike Ride
review.reviewBody:
The guides are top quality, respectful, and safe and will cater the ride according to your skill level!

Don't be intimidated - book a ride and get out there!  This area is an epic place to ride.

review.name: Exceeded expectations
review.reviewBody: We did the Tunnel Tour and absolutely loved the experience.  Our guides picked us up at our hotel and from the time we got into the van it was an outstanding adventure from giving the history of the area and landmarks to the outstanding hospitality....Dan,  Ken and DJ went above and beyond to personalize and make the trip one to remember.   We detoured a little to include a slight 20 minute climb to enhance the ride,  had a picnic including cupcakes for the 3 unexpected birthdays in the group.  The trip was worth every penny.  We will definitely be booking more tours with this group! Beyond our expectations!!

itemListElement.name: Seattle : Private Custom Walking Tour With A Guide (Private Tour)

name: Seattle : Private Custom Walking Tour With A Guide (Private Tour)
description:
Get to know the city through the eyes of a local guide. With no set itinerary, you can customize the tour or leave it to the local for an enlightening introduction to the city. With our private walking tours, you'll skip the mundane historical tours and experience the city through the eyes of a real local. Our local guides are passionate about their city and eager to share their knowledge and insights. The will offer an authentic and personal experience. By the end of the tour, you will feel comfortable navigating the city and confident that you have all the information you need to make the most of your stay.

- Private tour for just you and your group
- Your guide customizes your tour to your interests and personality 
- Get a deeper insight into Seattle life than possible alone 
- See Seattle through the eyes of a local and discover its hidden gems

Choose from 2, 3, 4, 6, and 8-hour tour options.

itemListElement.name: Waterfall Rappelling Canyoneering Adventure + Photo Package!

name: Waterfall Rappelling Canyoneering Adventure + Photo Package!
description:
Explore waterfalls from a new perspective! Wild Sky Adventure Guides guides unique adventures to canyons and waterfalls that are only accesible through canyoneering routes. 

Join our unforgettable expeditions amidst the wild mountains just outside Seattle! Our waterfall canyoneering adventures are tailored to beginners, the very experienced, and everyone in-between.

Wild Sky provides top-of-the-line equipment, including specialized SELAND canyoning wetsuits and safety gear, allowing you to immerse yourself in the adventure.

Descend awe-inspiring waterfalls, traverse through breathtaking canyons, and hone your downclimbing skills under the expert guidance of our International Canyoning Academy certified Swiftwater Canyoning Guide. Your safety is our first concern.

We offer a range of adventure options on our website. Contact us today, and together we can select the ideal adventure that aligns perfectly with your needs.

review.name: Best experience around!
review.reviewBody: Hands down the best experience I’ve ever had! I was a bit nervous trying something new but both guides were so patient and encouraging, the nerves went away quickly and the fun kicked in! I loved the variety of things you get to do such as repelling, sliding/jumping and even zip lining! This will 100% be an activity I do every summer!

review.name: Such a fun experience!
review.reviewBody: So so so much fun and the guides were so kind, knowledgeable, and helpful! I had no idea you could canyon here in Washington but you definitely can. The river they took us to had so many fun waterfalls to rappel and slide down, all unique and fun! Highly recommend.

review.name: Grew confidence in whitewater canyoning
review.reviewBody:
Back in July 2023, I got the chance to join a whitewater canyoning training led by Sam Keller from Wild Sky.

I have to say, it was a brilliant experience. 

Sam is the kind of pro you'd want to have with you while canyoning. He's got this calm, reassuring leadership style that makes you feel comfortable right away, and it's clear he loves teaching and seeing people grow.

He genuinely wants you to learn, have a good time, and, most importantly, stay safe. He lead the group to take on actually challenging actions that took our confidence in whitewater to a new level, all the while making sure safety was a top priority.

I want to give a huge shout-out to Sam for his guidance, and I can confidently recommend Wild Sky for anyone looking to have a blast while canyoning.

review.name: Seal Team Go!
review.reviewBody: We used this experience to get away from the kids. Yes, it was pricey, but they had ALL THE EQUIPMENT which was wonderful. They even had some extra stuff since i run on the cold side. They slowed down when i needed it and were wonderful with instructions. They have their own phones to take photos n videos of you so you dont have to worry about it. Despite my shoes being gr8 hiking shoes, they sucked for canyoneering. You really need something with grip in water. Needless to say, I googled their shoes and am buying them. They also had all the info on how I could further my own training. Awesome experience and if we have funds again next year, will most likely try a different experience! Thanks Austin and Sam, ya'll were wonderful, knowledgeable and hilarious.

review.name: Awesome guides lead to an awesome day out.
review.reviewBody: We had an awesome time with Sam and Wild Sky Adventure Guides. Both guides were friendly, knowledgeable, and professional. As a group of experienced canyoneers, they were able to tailor the trip to our skill set and provide a day worth remembering. They even sent us pics at the end. I would highly recommend them to anyone in the area.

review.name: Great Gear Kept Us Warm In September!
review.reviewBody:
I've been canyoneering before, but in different places, and never like this!

The canyon was better than anything I have ever done before! It was beautiful, engaging, and challenging.... But at the same time it was accessible and friendly.

The adventure takes a base level of fitness, you have to be able to hike all day. But even though we spent hours in and out of the water I never got cold!

Austin and Sam are obviously well trained, experienced, and run a great tour. They focused on safety from beginning to end. I felt challenged, but never unsafe. 

Make sure you bring dry shoes for after the trip. I forgot and had wet feet for the drive home!

review.name: Amazing rappels and slides on a stunning adventure
review.reviewBody: What an amazing day! Amazing rappels and slides on a stunning day. Sam and Austin were amazing guides helping my daughter (14) and I get our first taste of real canyoneering. From education about how to rappel and how to navigate the currents, Sam and Austin made us feel safe and secure while moving through waterfalls and rapids. Don't miss out!

review.name: Memorable Adventure!
review.reviewBody: Full day of fun! It was a little chilly out and I was worried about being cold but the wet suits they provided were warm so no issues there!! Some of our friends have been on canyon adventures with other companies and they were lowered slowly over a couple water falls so we were hoping for a bigger adventure with Wild Sky and they did not disappoint! We got to experience the water falls rapping ourselves and many slides. Sam and Austin were a blast! they will help you as much as you need or as little as you want. Highly recommend going with Wild Sky Adventure Guides - You will not be disappointed!

review.name: September was amazing to go with Wild Sky Adventure Guides. The  river was friendly and fun.
review.reviewBody: Samuel and Austin thank you so much for the fun time! My friends and I really appreciate everything. Amazing experince! We were in good hands at all times.

review.name: 100% the BEST adventure!
review.reviewBody: Words can barely express how amazing this adventure was. It’s definitely my #1 favorite memory! Sam was so patient with us and super knowledgeable and funny. It’s an all day adventure that you won’t regret!

name: Twilight Forks Washington Tour
description:
Twilight -Travel to Forks, Washington – home of the Twilight Saga.

Discover the magic of the rainiest town in the contiguous United States, just like Bella did! Explore the rain forest and beaches and just maybe, catch a glimpse of a vampire or werewolf! There’s lots for Forks Washington Twilight fans to see year-round including The Collection of props and costumes used in the movies, stop by the chamber to get a picture with Bella’s trucks, and download and print a Twilight map to take a self-guided tour of Twilight stops throughout town. Discover the charm of Olympic National Park on this full-day trip. 

Starting with a ferry ride to the nearest Seattle island -Welcome to our slice of Northwest hospitality and Olympic National Park charm!

This trip will have a maximum of 5 people per SUV or 14 people per van.

review.name: Worth it for the true Twilight Experience!
review.reviewBody: We did the Twilight Tour in Forks and it was wonderful! Dwight was full of awesome facts about the area and made sure that we got to see all the stops. I would highly recommend to anyone that wants to get the true Twilight experience!

review.name: Great Forks Tour!
review.reviewBody: Great tour for first timers here in Washington. Our Tour guide Dwight was awesome. Made for a very full day. Dwight is a great conversationalist and has awesome knowledge about Washington and Forks. Lots of gift shops there in forks also! Would go again and request Dwight!

review.name: Sure to Sparkle!
review.reviewBody: the Twilight Tours in Forks offer a unique and memorable experience for any Twilight enthusiast. The town’s small size and charm add to the allure, making it a perfect destination for a Twilight-themed adventure

review.name: Went to forks, la push, crescent lake. Absolutely breathtaking!
review.reviewBody: This trip was absolutely beautiful and amazing! Dwight is definitely the best tour guide i have ever had. He was extremely informative, nice and entertaining! Would 10/10 recommend to anyone taking this tour!!

review.name: Twilight Truck and Ruby Beach
review.reviewBody: Got to take pics with the truck from the movie Twilight.   There was great restaurant that served awesome sea food near by.  And we got to see what has become my favorite beach on our drive towards Forks!  Ruby Beach is awesome!

review.name: Good stop for fans
review.reviewBody: If you are a fan of the movie it is a must stop. The traveler information center was great and so friendly. We did the museum as well and it was ok, I am not a person to love looking at costumes so glad it wasn't a long wait that day. They had a nice selection so it is just more of a preference thing.
